    <!-- ==========================================
         OUR STORY
         ========================================== -->
    <section class="section" id="our-story" aria-labelledby="our-story-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="content-width">
          <div class="section-header">
            <span class="section-label">Our Story</span>
            <h2 id="our-story-heading">How we started</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="lead">
            The Still Me Project started with a question: what happens to identity when memory fades? We believed the answer mattered &mdash; not just to researchers, but to every family watching someone they love change. So we built an organization to find out.
          </p>
          <p>
            What began as informal conversations with families and caregivers has grown into a structured research and support initiative. We document real experiences, fund practical research, and develop tools that help families manage cognitive decline with dignity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ==========================================
         WHAT WE BELIEVE
         ========================================== -->
    <section class="section section--cream" id="beliefs" aria-labelledby="beliefs-heading">
      <div class="container">

        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-label">Our Values</span>
          <h2 id="beliefs-heading">What We Believe</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid-3">

          <!-- Belief 1 -->
          <article class="pillar-card">
            <div class="pillar-card__accent"></div>
            <div class="pillar-card__icon" aria-hidden="true">&hearts;</div>
            <h3>Identity outlasts memory</h3>
            <p>
              A person&rsquo;s identity is more than what they remember. Their character, relationships, and lifetime of experience remain, even when recall fades.
            </p>
          </article>

          <!-- Belief 2 -->
          <article class="pillar-card">
            <div class="pillar-card__accent"></div>
            <div class="pillar-card__icon" aria-hidden="true">&bull;</div>
            <h3>Families carry the weight</h3>
            <p>
              Cognitive decline affects entire families. Caregivers need real support &mdash; not platitudes.
            </p>
          </article>

          <!-- Belief 3 -->
          <article class="pillar-card">
            <div class="pillar-card__accent"></div>
            <div class="pillar-card__icon" aria-hidden="true">&diams;</div>
            <h3>Dignity is non-negotiable</h3>
            <p>
              Every person deserves to be treated with respect at every stage of cognitive change. This is not aspirational. It is foundational.
            </p>
          </article>

        </div>

      </div>
    </section>


